The paper deals with communication complexity, which is a topic in theoretical computer science and falls under the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) category. The use of information-theoretic methods suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.IT (Information Theory) category. The paper also involves manipulating distributions and probabilities, which are topics in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Finally, the paper discusses lower bounds on functions, which is a topic in cs.LG (Machine Learning).
